title.narrative: AFCC2/RI-East Africa Trade and Transport Facilitation Project

description.narrative: Project Development Objective (PDO): is to (i) enhance efficiency of customs agencies' clearance processes, for the EAC Partner States participating in the East Africa Customs Union, to facilitate trade; (ii) improve efficiency and reliability of transport and logistics services along the key corridors; and (iii) enhance safety in identified areas and reduce the Recipient#s fiscal transfers to railway institutions by rationalizing the work force on the Kenya-Uganda railway.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article V 5.01 (a) | Description :The Govt (KenTrade) prepares OP, FM and PM by FA effectiveness | Frequency:Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 - Section I-E Para 4 of FA dated August 3, 2011 | Description :The Govt shall not later thanSeptember 30, 2011 establish and thereafter maintain until completion of the project a ReMU to oversee the implementation f the RAP| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 - Section V. Other undertakings. | Description :The Govt (KPA) shall maintain, until the completionof the Project, in a commercial bank, a separate account into which it shall deposit its contribution for implementation of portISS | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 -Section I-E para 4 of FA dated August 3, 2011 | Description :The Govt shall not later than July 1,2012 open and maintain a Project Account in a commercial Bank and deposit amounts as shall berequired to pay its portion for theimplementation of the RAP. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.10 (a) (K) | Description :The Govt. shall implement and cause the Concessionaire to implement inaccordance with the Concession Agreement, the provisions of the EIA and the EMP. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.10 (b) (K) | Description :Govt. shall cause the Concessionaire to prepare an SMP and EMP within 12and 6 months of the Commencement date and to implement such plans in accordance with the timetables specified in them. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.11 (a)(a) (K) | Description :Prior to any activity which may involve increased trainactivity/involuntary displacement within the RAP safety corridor, the Govt.shall implement the RAP in all areas decided. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.11 (a)(b) (K) | Description :Prior to any activity which may involve increased trainactivity/involuntary displacement within the RAP safety corridor, the Got. shall ensure appropriate compensatory measures asnecessary. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.11 (b) (K) | Description :The Govt. shall during the implementation oof the Project, ensure thatinvoluntary resettlement shall be in accordance with the RAP, and only in the areas covered by the RAP | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.13 (a) (K) | Description :The Govt. shall cause the IAs to maintain policies & procedures adequate toenable it to monitor & evaluate continually, in accordance with the indicators in the DCA, the implementation of the Project |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.3.(b) (U) | Description :The Govt. shall establish & maintain during the Project, with ToRssatisfactory to IDA, a PSC, responsible for providing overall oversight and policy guidance, which composition is given in the DCA| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.4 (a)(i) (K) | Description :The Concessionaire shall identify staff they will employ through its owndiligence, in accordance with the provisions of the Concession Agreement (CA) | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.4 (a)(ii) (K) | Description :The Concessionaire shall, in accordance with the CA, define the terms ofemployment of KRC staff it will employ, which shall be no less favorable than those applicable prior to the commencement date |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.4 (a)(iii) (K) | Description :The Concessionaire shall offer letters of employment to staff selectedfor employment; staff not selected shall be retrenched by KRC in accordance with terms of retrenchment satisfactory to IDA |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.4 (a)(iv) (K) | Description :Staff of KRC selected by the Concessionaire for employment may declineany offer from the Concessionaire, such action being considered as voluntary retirement by the staff so declining the offer |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.4 (b) (K) | Description :KRC agrees that unless otherwise agreed upon,staff retrenched for theProject shall not for 3 years after retrenchment be reemployed by Govt., KRC and Concessionaire. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.5 (c) (K) | Description :Without prejudice to its laws, the Govt. shall cause MOT in coordinationwith KRC to carry out the retrenchment of eligible KRC employees in accordance with the Staff Retrenchment Manual | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.5 (d) (K) | Description :Except as otherwise agreed, the Govt. shall not amend, abrogate, waive orpermit such actions, the PIM & Staff RM or any provision thereof, in an adverse manner as detailed in the DCA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.5.(b) (U) | Description :The Govt. shall in coordination with URC carry out the concession of UgandaRailways with timetables, criteria, guidelines and procedures set forth in the PIM. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.6 (K) | Description :The Govt. shall implement a national cargo tracking system for goods transitingits territory along the Northern Corridor and its main trade routes with Tanzania. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.6 (R) | Description :The Govt. shall select the project auditors. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.6 (U) | Description :The Govt. shall select the project auditors. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.7 (R) | Description :The Govt. shall ensure timely preparation by CGPT, & submission to IDA of halfyearly progress of the implementation of part C of the Project. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.7 (g) (U) | Description :The SFA shall include the IA's obligation to ensure in the event of conflictbetween the SFA and the DCA, the latter shall prevail | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.8 (K) | Description :Govt. shall, within 90 days, furnish a report certified by independent auditorsconfirming that such payments were made to eligibleKRC employees. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.8 (a) (U) | Description :The Govt. shall prior to commencement of any civil works on inland containerdeport, cause URC, to implement the EIA and EMP in a form and substance satisfactory to the WB | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.8 (b) (U) | Description :Govt. shall cause the Concessionaire to prepare an SMP and EMP within 12 and6 months of the Commencement date and to implement such plans in accordance with the timetables specified in them. | Frequency:Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.9 (a) (U) | Description :Prior to any activity which may involve increased train activity/involuntarydisplacement within the RAP safety corridor, the Govt.shall implement the RAP in all areas decided. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 4.9 (b) (U) | Description :Prior to any activity which may involve increased train activity/involuntarydisplacement within the RAP safety corridor, the Got. shall ensure appropriate compensatory measures as necessary. | Frequency:Quarterly

title.narrative: Transit time along the NC (Mombas to Kigali) is reduced.
Rwanda meets the technical requirements to become a member of the EAC CU by end of project
Updated RAP is implemented in Kibera and Mukuru areas and safety zone created

target.value: 3km safety zone established in both Kibera and Mukuru

title.narrative: Regional Customs Systems Interconnection functions in all 4 participating countries

target.value: Substantial regional interconnection amongst participating EAC countries

actual.value: The IBM is being rolled out.

title.narrative: Decrease in border crossing time (in hours)

baseline.value: Malaba - KE 15; UG 30 hrsSerare/Isebania - No dataGatuna/Katuna - RW13 hrs UG no data

actual.value: Malaba, Average Kenya 5hours; Uganda, 6hours - inconsistency noted

title.narrative: Dwell time for standard 2 TEU container domestic cargo reduced
Seamless Cargo tracking is operatinal on the Northern Corridor

target.value: Cargo tracking operational in at least 2 countries on the NC.

actual.value: Achieved. Operational in KE and UG

title.narrative: Safety railway operation zones established in Kibera and Mukuru areas, Wagon Ferry services resume in Uganda

target.value: Safety zone established. Mv Kaawa operational

actual.value: Progress made in establishing safety railway operation zones in Kibera and Mukuru areas. MV Kaawaoperational

title.narrative: Railway ICD in Uganda built and functional
Kenya Railways Pension Scheme (KRPS) set up and is financially sustainable

target.value: Fully operatinal and Sustainable with known sources of revenue.

actual.value: KRPS already set up and operational with challenges in respect of the management of assets.

title.narrative: NSW establised in Kenya and CBS ESW at the Dar port

actual.value: Kenya's eSW was commissioned in Nov 2013. Tanzania's will be implemented through another DP support. Indicator dropeed in projrestructuring.

title.narrative: Variance of transit time through the Northern and Central Corridor is significantly reduced.
Customs procedures and documents are simplified in accordance with WCO standards.

target.value: Simplified documents as adjudged by WCO consultant

actual.value: Ongoing simplification to be assessed as part of the time release study

title.narrative: Corridor Authorities (NCTTCA and CCTTFA) set a transit traffic monitoring data base

actual.value: Transit traffic monitoring data base set up for both CC and NC
